title: Naming collision with react-native
body:
`react-router-native@4.0.0-beta.4` has some sort of naming collision with `react-native@0.41.1` this is output I get when trying to run ios simulator

```
Failed to build DependencyGraph: @providesModule naming collision:
  Duplicate module name: jsc-heap-capture
  Paths: /Users/ilja/Documents/repositories/projectTest/node_modules/react-native/local-cli/server/middleware/heapCapture/package.json collides with /Users/ilja/Documents/repositories/projectTest/node_modules/react-router-native/node_modules/react-native/local-cli/server/middleware/heapCapture/package.json

This error is caused by a @providesModule declaration with the same name across two different files.
Error: @providesModule naming collision:
  Duplicate module name: jsc-heap-capture
  Paths: /Users/ilja/Documents/repositories/projectTest/node_modules/react-native/local-cli/server/middleware/heapCapture/package.json collides with /Users/ilja/Documents/repositories/projectTest/node_modules/react-router-native/node_modules/react-native/local-cli/server/middleware/heapCapture/package.json

This error is caused by a @providesModule declaration with the same name across two different files.
    at HasteMap._updateHasteMap (/Users/ilja/Documents/repositories/projectTest/node_modules/react-native/packager/react-packager/src/node-haste/DependencyGraph/HasteMap.js:158:13)
    at p.getName.then.name (/Users/ilja/Documents/repositories/projectTest/node_modules/react-native/packager/react-packager/src/node-haste/DependencyGraph/HasteMap.js:133:31)
```

Possible related issue: https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/12183 but it seems like this one was fixed, leading me to think that there is an issue with react-native version used in native router, will updating it to 0.41.1 fix the issue?
